<h3>Article Submission</h3>
<p>Articles are added to the site by you writing a post on your site and then letting IndieWeb News know about it via a <a href="http://indiewebcamp.com/webmention">Webmention</a>.</p>

<h4>Write a Post</h4>

<p>Write a post on your own site, and mark it up with the Microformats markup for an <a href="http://microformats.org/wiki/microformats2#h-entry">h-entry</a>.</p>

<p>Somewhere in your article's markup, either add a <a href="http://indiewebcamp.com/rel-syndication">u-syndication</a> or <a href="http://indiewebcamp.com/u-category">u-category</a> link to the <a href="/publish">the IndieWeb News</a> publish endpoint.</p>

<h4>Send a Webmention</h4>

<p>Send a <a href="http://indiewebcamp.com/webmention">Webmention</a> notification to IndieWeb News. When that is received, IndieWeb News will fetch the page from your site and look for the <a href="http://microformats.org/wiki/microformats2#h-entry">h-entry</a> markup to find the post title and author.</p>

<hr/>
<h3>API</h3>
<ul>
  <li>/v1/domains</li>
  <li>/v1/domains/&lt;domain&gt;</li>
  <li>/v1/posts</li>
  <li>/v1/posts/&lt;postid&gt;</li>
</ul>

